    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.21.75-77_0001b" />
                <note type="curatorial">14-2
                Ev.</note>
                
          <fw type="letterhead">      
                <hi rend="caps">SKYRIM FARM</hi>
              <lb/>  
                <hi rend="caps">ROUTE 7</hi>
              <lb/>  
                <hi rend="caps">COLUMBIA, MISSOURI</hi>
          </fw>
                
              <opener>  
                <dateline>5-11-'58</dateline>
                
                
                
                <salute>Dear Lucile &amp; Bower:</salute>
              </opener>
                <p>Thanks for the invitation to be a guest in your home after June 8. I will return from Yankton about June 7, and then I can come to you for a week or more. I think this is a good plan, as it will save you much coming and going. I do hope, however, that we may be at Skyrim once or twice. If we give our time to the job, much can be done in even one week.</p>
                    <fw type="curatorial">75</fw>
                    
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.21.75-77_0001a"/>    
                    <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                    
                    <p>Alice &amp; the children will be leaving (with a load of horses) next Wednesday. (This is Sunday). I'm glad I can tell the children I'll be coming down to them in a short while.</p>
              
                <p>I'm reading the <hi rend="caps">MS</hi> &#8212; Chap IV. <hi rend="underline">Good job</hi>! Two or three corrections as to facts &#8212; easy to make. Will pass the <hi rend="caps">MS</hi> on to Dr. Reid.</p>
                
             <closer>
                <salute>Affectionately,</salute>
                <signed>John N.</signed>
             </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            <div1 type="envelope">
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.21.75-77_0002"/>
                
              <ab type="return">  
                John Neihardt                             
                Route 7
                Columbia,<hi rend="underline">Mo.</hi>
              </ab>
              <note type="authorial"><hi rend="italic">Air Mail</hi></note>
                
              <ab type="postmark">COLUMBIA. MO. MAY <unclear/> 4-PM 1958
              PRAY FOR PEACE</ab>  
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>U.S. POSTAGE 3Â¢ IN GOD WE TRUST LIBERTY</p>
                </figure>
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>3 Cent Stamp</figDesc>
                    <p>UNITED STATES POSTAGE THREE 3 CENTS</p>
                </figure>
                
              <ab type="address">
                  <address>
                <addrLine>Dr. and Mrs. Bower-Aly,</addrLine>
                <addrLine><del/>2094 Hilyard,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Eugene,</addrLine>
                <addrLine>Oregon.</addrLine>
                  </address>
              </ab>
                
                <note type="authorial"><hi rend="italic">Air Mail</hi></note>
                <fw type="curatorial">76</fw>
                
             <pb facs="nei.j4c.21.75-77_0003"/>
                <note type="authorial">I've just completed the <hi rend="caps">MS</hi>. Excellent writing! If what you are saying is true, you know how 
                <hi rend="underline">I</hi> explain it &#8212; when it really happens. J. N.</note>
                
                
                
                
            </div1>
